OL,3,CThousands more shoplifting offences
OL,4,Crecorded in 'epidemic of retail crime'
OL,6,FShoplifting offences across the South
OL,7,FWest have risen by 31%, according to
OL,8,Fthe latest data from the Office for
OL,9,FNational Statistics.
OL,11,FMore than 38,000 offences were
OL,12,Frecorded across the region in the 12
OL,13,Fmonths up to June 2024, up by almost a
OL,14,Fthird compared to the previous year.
OL,16,FThe figures showed more than 16,500
OL,17,Fshoplifting cases in the Avon and
OL,18,FSomerset Police area - a rise of 40%.
