OL,3,CThousands more shoplifting offences
OL,4,Crecorded in 'epidemic of retail crime'
OL,6,FPaddy Lillis, the union's general
OL,7,Fsecretary, said: "This increase in
OL,8,Fshoplifting is further evidence that
OL,9,Fwe are facing an epidemic of retail
OL,10,Fcrime.
OL,12,FUsdaw's 2023 annual survey of more
OL,13,Fthan 5,500 shop workers found that 60%
OL,14,Fhad suffered incidents of violence,
OL,15,Fthreats and abuse that were triggered
OL,16,Fby shoplifting and armed robbery.
OL,18,FMr Lillis added: "This is in no way a
OL,19,Fvictimless crime, with weapons and
OL,20,Fviolence used to ensure these
OL,21,Fcriminals are not stopped.
